      "text": [
        ": قُلْتُ لِأَبِي جَعْفَرٍ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ مَا أَدْنَى اَلنَّصْبِ قَالَ \"أَنْ يَبْتَدِعَ اَلرَّجُلُ شَيْئاً فَيُحِبَّ عَلَيْهِ وَ يُبْغِضَ عَلَيْهِ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.4956 - Al-Hasan ibn Mahbub narrated from Abdullah ibn Sinan, from Abu Hamzah, who said: I asked Abu Ja'far Imam Muhammad ibn Ali Al-Baqir (as), \"What is the least form of (nasb) hostility (towards the Ahlulbayt (as))?\"\nImam (as) replied: \"It is when a man innovates something, and then loves because of it and hates because of it.\""
        ]
      }
    },
